article.description: Manley leads Kent State past Toledo 67-60
article.headline: Manley leads Kent State past Toledo 67-60
article.linkText: Manley leads Kent State past Toledo 67-60
article.story: KENT, Ohio -- Devareaux Manley scored 21 points and hit two key 3-pointers in the final five minutes, helping Kent State defeat Toledo 67-60 on Wednesday night. Kris Brewer had 18 points on 8-of-12 shooting, Derek Jackson scored 10 and Khaliq Spicer had eight with nine boards for the Golden Flashes (13-5, 4-1 Mid-American). Kent State shot 48.1 percent from the field in winning its fourth straight. Nathan Boothe and Jonathan Williams each scored 12 points for Toledo (10-8, 2-3), which also shot 48.1 percent, but made just 5 of 13 free throws and 3 of 16 3-pointers. Manley took over down the stretch, making two layups to take the lead with 6:31 remaining. Manley sank a 3-pointer, then responded to Williams' jumper with another trey, pushing Kent State's lead to 59-53 with 3:05 left. The Rockets pulled within three late, but Kent State nailed 6 of 8 free throws to cap it.
